      <hedline>
        <hl1>Gathering</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By RICHARD PERRY</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Photo of motorcyclists assembled in Paterson, NJ, for annual motorcycle Mass and blessing of bikes by Msgr Mark Giordani, Harley-Davidson enthusiast who founded Christian Riders motorcycle club</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>On the first Sunday of May, motorcyclists assemble on Main Street in Paterson, N.J., near the Roman Catholic Cathedral of St. John the Baptist for the annual motorcycle Mass and blessing of the bikes. Msgr. Mark Giordani, a Harley-Davidson enthusiast who founded the Christian Riders motorcycle club, started the event in 1969 at his first parish, and he has been celebrating the Mass and blessing at the cathedral since 1987.</p>
      </block>
